comments: Tatum (BOS) jumps alongside Maxey's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before releasing the pass.
Tatum (BOS) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Brown (BOS) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) and Smart (BOS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Smart (BOS) brings his arms toward Harris (PHI) and marginal contact occurs as Smart releases away to roll.
Williams (BOS) initiates contact with Harden's (PHI) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) contests the shot and initiates contact with Tatum's (BOS) body, affecting the jump shot attempt.

Replay review of the shot clock violation called on BOS pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Tatum's (BOS) shot does not make contact with the rim and BOS maintains possession when the shot clock expires.
Tucker (PHI) establishes himself in Williams' (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Horford (BOS) is legally in the lane for more than three seconds since he is actively guarding Tucker (PHI) when he enters and then exits the lane and then again when he guards him in the corner.
Brown (BOS) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward Embiid (PHI) and is not in a legal guarding position as contact occurs during Embiid's upward shooting motion.
Smart (BOS) avoids contact with Harris (PHI) after the dribble-hand-off.
Harris (PHI) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
Melton (PHI) legally contests Tatum's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
After replay review, it was determined that the game clock expired before the ball left Embiid's (PHI) hands.
